-- Get detections for objects classified as CV/Nova by the stochastic light curve classifier (highest probability class)
-- Only include objects with ndet <= 50
-- Only consider r-band detections (fid = 2)
-- Collect corrected difference magnitude (magpsf_corr) and PSF corrected magnitude (magpsf_corr)
-- For each object, calculate the maximum rise from minimum in magpsf_corr among its detections
-- Return first 1000 rows, ordered by object identifier
 WITH selected_oids AS
  (SELECT oid
   FROM probability
   WHERE classifier_name = 'lc_classifier_stochastic'
     AND class_name = 'CV/Nova'
     AND ranking = 1
     AND oid IN
       (SELECT oid
        FROM OBJECT
        WHERE ndet <= 50 ) ),
      r_band_detections AS
  (SELECT d.oid AS object_identifier,
          d.candid AS candidate_identifier,
          d.fid AS f_id,
          d.ra,
          d.dec,
          d.magpsf_corr, -- corrected difference magnitude (PSF)
 d.sigmapsf_corr, -- error of the apparent magnitude assuming point like source
 d.magpsf_corr AS psf_corrected_magnitude, -- same as magpsf_corr in this schema
 d.sigmapsf_corr AS psf_corrected_magnitude_error
   FROM detection d
   WHERE d.oid IN
       (SELECT oid
        FROM selected_oids)
     AND d.fid = 2 -- r-band filter
),
      mag_stats AS
  (SELECT object_identifier,
          MAX(magpsf_corr) AS max_mag,
          MIN(magpsf_corr) AS min_mag,
          (MAX(magpsf_corr) - MIN(magpsf_corr)) AS max_rise
   FROM r_band_detections
   GROUP BY object_identifier)
SELECT r.object_identifier,
       r.candidate_identifier,
       r.f_id,
       r.ra,
       r.dec,
       r.magpsf_corr AS corrected_difference_magnitude,
       r.sigmapsf_corr AS corrected_difference_magnitude_error,
       r.psf_corrected_magnitude,
       r.psf_corrected_magnitude_error,
       m.max_rise
FROM r_band_detections r
JOIN mag_stats m ON r.object_identifier = m.object_identifier
ORDER BY r.object_identifier
